Tom, I fully agree. But it takes two to talk. I gave up on Cook because he never, never, answered any of my questions.<br>
Instead he called me names, and has organized his pack of hyena's to make sure no one else gets heard on this site.<br>
I find that to be repugnant at best. Talk about stiffling free speech and the free trade of ideas and opinions. Where are you and the others in fighting this?  It reminds me of the Germans, during WWII, who said: &quot;Jews, what Jews, We did not see any misbehavior with the Jews.&quot;<br><br>
What happened to ClassLass?  The treatment given to VietSon made me want to scream. And you, my old friend, seem swayed by these new boys, and no longer hold your old ideals as high. I hope I am wrong. But it takes strength to stand up to a site that seems to be a majority opinion, only because they have bullied out the rest of the &quot;thinkers&quot;.<br><br>
I will never give up the ghost of critical thinking, of challenging, of opposition. I will never yield to the ghost of the swaggering John &quot;Cook&quot; Wayne, twin machine guns under his arms, bragging about his bravado. Never. We faught to long to learn how to talk to each other, to understand each other, yet now, you fail me. You can't or won't see what is happening. Is that a &quot;vet thing&quot; that you must stand with your brother vet, right or wrong, because he is a vet, even though he is a bully and a facist?  Come on Tom, I know you are better than that.<br><br>
Freedom of expression, freedom of speech, freedom from the tyrany of the hyena pack, is what I am all about, and I thought you were too.  I think you still are.  Think about it.
